verbs.description: outpopulate (third-person singular simple present outpopulates, present participle outpopulating, simple past and past participle outpopulated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To surpass in population; to outnumber.
examples: Antiabortion activists pointed out that immigrant families, many of them Catholic, were larger and would soon outpopulate native-born white Yankees and threaten their political power.
